What Multer Is

Multer is an Express middleware specifically designed for handling:
multipart/form-data
File uploads

👉 It does three main things:
Parses incoming request
Extracts files and text fields
Stores files (disk or memory)

Multipart Form-Data (Simple Explanation)
Think of it like a package with multiple compartments:
[ username = "john" ]
[ profilePic = image.jpg ]
[ resume = file.pdf ]
Each part:
Has its own headers (name, type)
Is separated by boundaries
👉 Unlike JSON:
{ "file": ??? } ❌ not possible
👉 Instead:
Content-Type: multipart/form-data ✔


Upload Lifecycle (Clear Flow)
Client selects file
        ↓
Form sends multipart/form-data request
        ↓
Express receives request
        ↓
Multer intercepts request
        ↓
Parses fields → req.body
Parses files → req.file / req.files
        ↓
Stores file (disk/cloud)
        ↓
Controller uses file info
        ↓
Response sent back





